    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nHi! I've upgraded the system today and looks like new version of NeoVim [introduced some updates](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/c294bc397b6a50fa3e1709246250e8b394555ce1) to the theming process. I have a theme loading as a Lazy plugin:\n\n```\n  {\n    'projekt0n/github-nvim-theme',\n    name = 'github-theme',\n    lazy = false,    -- make sure we load this during startup if it is your main colorscheme\n    priority = 1000, -- make sure to load this before all the other start plugins\n    config = function()\n      require('github-theme').setup({\n        -- ...\n      })\n\n      vim.cmd('colorscheme github_light_colorblind')\n      -- vim.cmd('colorscheme github_light')\n      -- vim.cmd('colorscheme github_dark_colorblind')\n      -- vim.cmd('colorscheme github_dark')\n    end,\n  },\n```\nAnd when I initially start NeoVim, everything's fine, I see correct theme\n\n<img width=\"1230\" height=\"930\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/651dd5cb-c19b-479e-8a88-9c3f1c1adbc1\" />\n\nBut if I push NeoVim to background with Ctrl-Z, after returning back it will reset to 'default':\n\n<img width=\"1230\" height=\"930\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/561f3205-4745-45e5-8241-fc6e5e15f8fa\" />\n\nWhile filing the issue, I've found out that the same behavior repeats even if I resize my terminal window with NeoVim opened.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nMaybe it's not a bug, just a new behavior, if so, can you please tell, how do I properly configure my theme now? If I need to have different themes for dark and light mode, it's okay, I just don't know how to do it yet.\n\nThanks a lot!\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nnot applicable\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nNixOS 26.05\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nAlacritty 0.17.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nnixpkgs",
