            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "\nI took a look at that overcomplicated collection of code named projekt0n/github-nvim-theme. I am not suprised if something doesn't work as expected, if a bunch of autocmds in combination with vim.schedule_wrap is required to provide a colorscheme. just use a normal colortheme that sets colors.\n \nI cannot reproduce the \"bug\" with the nvim-build and builtin-colorschemes and some \"normal\" external lua based colorschemes. fg/bg jobcontrol doesn't affect the colorscheme on my system.\n\n",
